10:34.960 --> 10:36.930
Just you.

10:37.130 --> 10:38.800
Sit down.

10:39.000 --> 10:42.040
[indistinct chatter]

10:46.910 --> 10:48.740
[door opens]

10:49.640 --> 10:51.580
Phoebe. Hey, Phoebe.

10:51.780 --> 10:53.580
- What'd they ask you?
- About the fire.

10:53.780 --> 10:54.980
You know, they think
it's one of us.

10:55.180 --> 10:56.620
What'd you tell them?

10:56.820 --> 10:59.490
That I think it was you.

10:59.690 --> 11:01.690
Hey, Harlan, steal
anyone's boyfriend lately?

11:01.890 --> 11:03.160
Just yours.

11:05.360 --> 11:06.960
- She was fucking with me,
right?

11:07.160 --> 11:08.700
[scoffs]

11:08.900 --> 11:09.830
<i>* *</i>

11:10.030 --> 11:11.130
We should ask for a lawyer.

11:11.330 --> 11:12.700
- You know what happens
when we do that?

11:12.900 --> 11:13.940
They arrest us.

11:14.140 --> 11:15.100
I'm not getting arrested.

11:15.300 --> 11:16.510
Sorry, but if I have to,

11:16.700 --> 11:17.570
I'm telling them everything
they want to know.

11:17.770 --> 11:19.580
Everything?

11:19.770 --> 11:21.480
We need a story.

11:21.680 --> 11:23.510
Something simple.
We all stick to it.

11:23.710 --> 11:24.680
Like we were working

11:24.880 --> 11:25.650
on a school project
or something?

11:25.850 --> 11:28.120
- No.
Jesus, Luna.

11:28.320 --> 11:29.850
- Like we were smoking weed.
- But that's a crime.

11:30.050 --> 11:33.520
- Which makes it sound like
we're telling the truth.

11:33.720 --> 11:35.190
- Nobody gives a shit
about a couple of kids

11:35.390 --> 11:36.590
smoking in the woods.

11:36.790 --> 11:38.160
I don't smoke weed.

11:38.360 --> 11:39.190
I tried edibles once
and all it did

11:39.390 --> 11:41.360
was make my anxiety worse.

11:41.560 --> 11:43.870
- So you're that guy?
- Pretty much.

11:44.070 --> 11:50.170
<i>* *</i>

11:50.370 --> 11:51.570
Hey. Did you tell them?

11:51.770 --> 11:53.980
- Tell them what?
- What you saw on the highway.

11:54.180 --> 11:56.480
I didn't see shit.

11:56.680 --> 11:58.210
<i>* *</i>

11:58.410 --> 12:02.620
[heartbeat thudding]

12:02.820 --> 12:04.520
- Why is your heart beating
so fast?

12:04.720 --> 12:07.120
[heartbeat thudding]

12:07.320 --> 12:09.930
That guy?
That's your type?

12:10.130 --> 12:12.160
- Fuck off.
- [chuckles]

12:12.360 --> 12:14.530
<i>* *</i>

12:14.730 --> 12:18.800
- Everett Lang.
You're up.

12:19.000 --> 12:21.300
Let's go.

12:29.240 --> 12:32.080
<i>[tense music]</i>

12:32.280 --> 12:39.150
<i>* *</i>

12:50.300 --> 12:51.200
[sighs]

12:51.400 --> 12:52.970
<i>* *</i>

12:53.170 --> 12:55.300
- Thanks, Miller.
We got it from here.

12:55.500 --> 12:56.640
[sighs]

12:56.840 --> 13:02.950
<i>* *</i>

13:03.140 --> 13:06.180
<i>[white noise machine hissing]</i>

13:07.920 --> 13:09.820
It's a white noise machine.

13:10.020 --> 13:12.550
Keep the distractions out.

13:12.750 --> 13:15.590
- I know.
My therapist uses one.

13:15.790 --> 13:17.730
Mine too.

13:20.300 --> 13:24.070
Everett, your friend Connor
is missing.

13:24.270 --> 13:25.370
[cast thuds]

13:27.270 --> 13:28.870
It, uh, looks like
he pulled his leg

13:29.070 --> 13:30.140
right out of this cast

13:30.340 --> 13:33.480
which, I imagine,
was not easy to do.

13:33.670 --> 13:34.980
Must have been
in quite a hurry.

13:35.180 --> 13:36.550
What do you mean missing?

13:36.740 --> 13:37.880
No one can seem to find him

13:38.080 --> 13:39.410
and he's not answering
his phone.

13:39.610 --> 13:41.680
In other words, missing.

13:41.880 --> 13:43.550
- His parents
are understandably concerned.

13:43.750 --> 13:44.890
They have no idea why

13:45.090 --> 13:46.860
he would just
leave the hospital like that.

13:47.060 --> 13:49.420
- Yeah. Kind of like
what you did the other night.

13:49.620 --> 13:54.260
- Do you think Connor had
anything to do with the fire?

13:54.460 --> 13:57.230
<i>- No. He-he would never</i>
<i>do anything like that.</i>

13:57.430 --> 13:59.730
- Do you know someone who would
do something like that?

14:01.840 --> 14:03.110
- Wait, you guys are looking
for him, right?

14:03.300 --> 14:04.940
Like, to make sure he's okay?

14:05.140 --> 14:08.110
- Actually, Everett,
let's get back to you.

14:08.310 --> 14:10.950
- We have a witness
who can place you

14:11.150 --> 14:15.250
and Blake Navarro
and Harlan and Luna Briggs

14:15.450 --> 14:18.220
very close to the point
of origin of the fire.

14:18.420 --> 14:21.290
Earlier today.
This stone ridge right here.

14:21.490 --> 14:22.990
Can you tell me
what you guys were doing there?

14:23.190 --> 14:24.690
- Same thing
everyone does there.

14:24.890 --> 14:26.130
We were smoking.

14:26.330 --> 14:28.200
- Smoking what?
- Weed.

14:28.400 --> 14:31.270
- How often do you smoke?
- Like, barely ever.

14:31.470 --> 14:33.500
- And what exactly
were you smoking?

14:33.700 --> 14:36.340
- Weed.
- Right.

14:36.540 --> 14:38.240
Pipe? Joint? Blunt?

14:38.440 --> 14:39.240
An edible.

14:39.440 --> 14:40.310
[groans]

14:41.280 --> 14:42.910
You were smoking an edible?

14:44.180 --> 14:46.380
- Everett, just say
that we smoked

14:46.580 --> 14:47.520
and you took an edible.

14:47.720 --> 14:50.250
[words echoing]
Fucking please.

14:50.450 --> 14:53.390
- They smoked.
I took an edible.

14:53.590 --> 14:54.960
<i>[tense ethereal tones]</i>

14:55.160 --> 14:56.790
Did you hear that?

14:56.990 --> 14:59.590
Everett, can you hear me?

14:59.790 --> 15:02.430
Yes.

15:02.630 --> 15:03.800
Yes what?

15:04.000 --> 15:06.000
- Yes.
That's all we were doing.

15:06.200 --> 15:07.600
<i>- Harlan...</i>
- [gasps]

15:07.800 --> 15:09.000
<i>* *</i>

15:09.200 --> 15:13.040
- I can hear you too.
- Holy shit.

15:13.240 --> 15:15.610
You can hear what I'm saying
right now?

15:15.810 --> 15:17.750
- So can I.
<i>- Oh, my God.</i>

15:17.950 --> 15:21.820
[gasps]
This is fucking amazing.

15:22.020 --> 15:28.860
<i>* *</i>

15:29.720 --> 15:33.330
<i>Everett. Listen to me.</i>

15:33.530 --> 15:35.530
<i>I'm gonna tell you</i>
<i>exactly what to say.</i>

15:35.730 --> 15:42.770
<i>* *</i>

15:43.170 --> 15:45.010
Everett, are you all right?

15:45.210 --> 15:46.910
- Why do you keep asking
about me?

15:47.110 --> 15:49.110
Something happened to Connor
and you need to find him.

15:49.310 --> 15:50.280
I understand your concern.

15:50.480 --> 15:52.450
We have local PD out
looking for him.

15:52.650 --> 15:54.250
But it does make me wonder.

15:54.450 --> 15:56.090
Is there a reason Connor
might not want to be found?

15:56.280 --> 15:57.620
<i>- Everett,</i>
<i>forget about Connor.</i>

15:57.820 --> 15:59.450
Answer the questions so we can
get the hell out of here.

15:59.650 --> 16:01.760
[door opens]

16:01.960 --> 16:03.790
Who you talkin' to?

16:03.990 --> 16:06.330
No one.

16:06.530 --> 16:10.830
- You mean no one
on the other side of this wall?

16:11.570 --> 16:14.540
[knocks on wall]

16:14.740 --> 16:15.540
<i>* *</i>

16:15.740 --> 16:17.810
You want to talk?

16:18.010 --> 16:21.040
<i>* *</i>

16:21.240 --> 16:22.950
- Talk to me.
- I want a lawyer.

16:23.140 --> 16:24.480
[sighs] Shit, Everett.

16:24.680 --> 16:25.950
You're not under arrest.

16:26.150 --> 16:27.180
Okay, fine.

16:27.380 --> 16:28.250
Then I-I want to talk
to my parents.

16:28.450 --> 16:29.280
[sighs]

16:29.480 --> 16:31.620
- Go ahead.
Give 'em a call.

16:31.820 --> 16:37.790
<i>* *</i>

16:37.990 --> 16:39.290
[sighs]

16:39.490 --> 16:46.370
<i>* *</i>

16:49.400 --> 16:53.040
[sighs]
Can I get a lawyer instead?

16:53.240 --> 16:54.510
- You struggle
with some pretty bad anxiety,

16:54.710 --> 16:57.880
- don't you?
- Yeah, you could say that.

16:58.080 --> 17:00.220
- Used to hit me the hardest
right before I went to sleep.

17:00.420 --> 17:01.250
[sighs]

17:01.450 --> 17:03.520
Do you know why that happens?

17:03.720 --> 17:08.720
- Um, something to do
with survival.

17:08.920 --> 17:10.060
<i>* *</i>

17:10.260 --> 17:12.230
It's a threat response.

17:12.430 --> 17:13.730
Right before we go to sleep,

17:13.930 --> 17:16.570
<i>our brain goes into a state</i>
<i>of hypervigilance</i>

17:16.760 --> 17:18.400
<i>because back</i>
<i>when we were living in caves,</i>

17:18.600 --> 17:20.270
<i>sleep was the time</i>
<i>we were most likely</i>

17:20.470 --> 17:23.140
<i>to get eaten</i>
<i>by saber-toothed tiger.</i>

17:23.340 --> 17:26.310
So now we lie in bed
staring at the ceiling,

17:26.510 --> 17:29.440
feeling that anxiety
race through our bodies

17:29.640 --> 17:31.480
because we're waiting
to be attacked by a predator

17:31.680 --> 17:34.620
that hasn't existed
in 10,000 years.

17:34.820 --> 17:39.320
- Okay, well, I'm not worried
about a saber-toothed tiger.

17:39.520 --> 17:41.620
- What are you worried about,
Everett?

17:41.820 --> 17:44.130
<i>* *</i>

17:44.330 --> 17:47.060
What keeps you up at night?

17:47.260 --> 17:49.430
<i>* *</i>

17:49.630 --> 17:52.100
- I'm not talking
to any of you.

17:52.300 --> 17:55.140
- I want a lawyer.
- Fine.

17:55.340 --> 17:57.810
Let's go get you a lawyer.

17:58.010 --> 18:01.580
Get your ass up.

18:01.780 --> 18:03.550
- Let's go.
- Get your--

18:03.740 --> 18:04.880
hey!

18:05.080 --> 18:06.280
[grunts]

18:06.480 --> 18:10.420
- And you just
assaulted a police officer.

18:10.620 --> 18:12.850
That's not what I saw.

18:13.050 --> 18:15.360
Get your hands off my son,
officer,

18:15.560 --> 18:18.560
or we will have a conversation
about assault.

18:18.760 --> 18:21.460
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

18:21.660 --> 18:27.870
<i>* *</i>

18:28.740 --> 18:31.910
- Yes, of course.
I told them my dad's a lawyer.

18:32.110 --> 18:33.180
<i>- I want names</i>
<i>and badge numbers.</i>

18:33.370 --> 18:34.580
<i>I'm calling the DA.</i>

18:34.780 --> 18:36.680
<i>They can't get away</i>
<i>with this shit.</i>

18:38.010 --> 18:39.550
<i>You're coming home, right?</i>

18:40.950 --> 18:41.980
It's the weekend, Dad.

18:42.180 --> 18:45.250
No.
I'm obviously not coming home.

18:45.450 --> 18:47.290
<i>- Careful, sweetheart.</i>
<i>[dashboard chimes]</i>

18:47.490 --> 18:50.360
- Shit. Wait.
Dad, hold on.

19:11.250 --> 19:13.010
Unbelievable.

19:20.420 --> 19:22.020
<i>[dashboard chiming]</i>

19:22.220 --> 19:23.760
Dad, I got a flat tire.

19:23.960 --> 19:25.730
I think someone slashed it.

19:25.930 --> 19:28.330
<i>I'm coming to pick you up.</i>

19:28.530 --> 19:30.370
- [slashing, tire hissing]
- [gasps]

19:30.570 --> 19:33.500
<i>[tense music]</i>
<i>[dashboard chiming]</i>

19:33.700 --> 19:37.010
- What the fuck?
<i>- Phoebe?</i>

19:37.200 --> 19:39.940
<i>Phoebe!</i>
<i>[dashboard chiming]</i>

19:40.140 --> 19:42.940
[air hisses]

19:43.140 --> 19:50.220
<i>* *</i>

19:54.620 --> 19:55.890
[locks click]

19:56.090 --> 19:57.760
<i>* *</i>

19:57.960 --> 19:59.690
- [slashing, tire hissing]
- [gasps]

19:59.890 --> 20:02.760
<i>[dashboard chiming]</i>

20:02.960 --> 20:04.930
<i>* *</i>

20:05.130 --> 20:07.070
<i>Phoebe, what's going on?</i>

20:07.270 --> 20:10.110
Dad, the tires are flat.

20:10.300 --> 20:11.770
<i>Which ones?</i>

20:11.970 --> 20:13.110
- [slashing, tire hissing]
- [gasps]

20:13.310 --> 20:15.710
<i>[dashboard chiming]</i>

20:15.910 --> 20:18.050
<i>* *</i>

20:18.250 --> 20:19.450
All of them.

20:19.650 --> 20:20.880
<i>* *</i>

20:21.080 --> 20:21.920
[gasps]

20:22.120 --> 20:23.290
<i>* *</i>

20:23.480 --> 20:25.520
<i>[car alarm blaring]</i>

20:25.720 --> 20:31.860
<i>* *</i>

20:36.060 --> 20:38.100
[sighs]

20:38.300 --> 20:39.830
Mr. Briggs.

20:40.030 --> 20:41.570
Mr. Briggs.

20:44.440 --> 20:46.780
- Are you the one in charge?
- Kristin Ramsey.

20:46.970 --> 20:48.280
We're very glad you're okay.

20:48.480 --> 20:50.850
- You're not talking to my kids
without a lawyer present.

20:51.050 --> 20:52.410
- My lawyer.
- Fine.

20:52.610 --> 20:54.880
- Call him in.
- Her.

20:55.080 --> 20:56.450
And unless you're charging
someone with a crime,

20:56.650 --> 20:58.220
they are free to go, right?

20:58.420 --> 20:59.950
Not if we arrest them.

21:00.150 --> 21:02.090
<i>* *</i>

21:02.290 --> 21:03.490
- Uh, Mr. Briggs,
we were just

21:03.690 --> 21:05.190
asking the kids
a couple questions.

21:05.390 --> 21:06.700
They were kind enough
to volunteer.

21:06.890 --> 21:09.460
Not me.

21:09.660 --> 21:12.130
I didn't volunteer for shit.

21:12.330 --> 21:13.940
<i>* *</i>

21:14.130 --> 21:15.470
[whispering] Dad.

21:15.670 --> 21:18.170
What?

21:18.370 --> 21:19.810
- Dad, they need to come
with us.

21:20.010 --> 21:22.340
- Why?
- Mr. Briggs.

21:22.540 --> 21:25.910
- Because...
- Mr. Briggs.

21:26.110 --> 21:27.780
Because they're like us.

21:27.980 --> 21:30.790
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

21:30.990 --> 21:37.860
<i>* *</i>

21:45.930 --> 21:47.640
- But then the bite healed
and so did hers,

21:47.840 --> 21:49.370
except Connor's
didn't look the same

21:49.570 --> 21:50.640
and it didn't heal.

21:50.840 --> 21:52.140
- Who's Connor?
- My friend.

21:52.340 --> 21:53.410
He called me from the hospital

21:53.610 --> 21:54.710
and said something
was trying to kill him

21:54.910 --> 21:55.640
just like the voice
on the phone told us.

21:55.840 --> 21:56.810
And now nobody can find him.

21:57.010 --> 21:58.680
- You have no idea
who called you?

21:58.880 --> 22:00.250
He knew my name.

22:00.450 --> 22:01.420
Told me to leave the hospital.

22:01.620 --> 22:02.820
He said it was gonna try
and kill me

22:03.020 --> 22:04.490
before the next full moon.

22:08.190 --> 22:11.030
Um, where are we going?

22:11.230 --> 22:13.230
You're coming back with us.

22:13.430 --> 22:14.730
- I have to get
back to the motel.

22:14.930 --> 22:16.330
We have to talk first.

22:16.530 --> 22:18.170
I'll take you both
wherever you need to go,

22:18.370 --> 22:21.300
but I need to hear
the whole story.

22:21.500 --> 22:23.070
Whatever the two of you
saw on the highway,

22:23.270 --> 22:27.340
whatever bit you...

22:27.540 --> 22:29.040
came after me too.

22:29.240 --> 22:31.780
<i>* *</i>

22:31.980 --> 22:33.110
Did you see it?

22:33.310 --> 22:35.850
<i>* *</i>

22:36.050 --> 22:37.220
I don't know what I saw.

22:37.420 --> 22:39.720
Something hit the truck
and I ran.

22:39.920 --> 22:41.920
- That's what pushed you
over the fire line.

22:42.120 --> 22:44.360
Was it...him?

22:44.560 --> 22:46.130
<i>* *</i>

22:46.330 --> 22:48.100
Was it our real father?

22:48.300 --> 22:54.370
<i>* *</i>

22:55.440 --> 22:56.770
Hey, can somebody tell me

22:56.970 --> 22:58.810
why we're not arresting
those little shits?

22:59.010 --> 23:00.680
<i>* *</i>

23:00.880 --> 23:02.910
- Because I don't think
they set the fire.

23:03.110 --> 23:05.380
- So how come every word
out of their mouths

23:05.580 --> 23:07.380
sounds like a fuckin' lie?

23:07.580 --> 23:09.180
- Well, first of all,
they're teenagers.

23:09.380 --> 23:10.550
All they do is lie.

23:10.750 --> 23:12.920
Second, they probably
are hiding something.

23:13.120 --> 23:15.520
Just might not have anything
to do with the fire.

23:15.720 --> 23:17.530
- Well, maybe you should
have pushed harder.

23:17.730 --> 23:19.530
Five minutes
in a room with them,

23:19.730 --> 23:21.760
I'd have had a confession.

23:21.960 --> 23:23.000
- Hey, Miller,
you're shift is over.

23:23.200 --> 23:24.430
You're done.

23:24.630 --> 23:26.970
I'll see you at the bar.
Come on.

23:27.170 --> 23:30.840
Officer, speaking of pushing,

23:31.040 --> 23:32.740
if I see you
so much as lay a hand

23:32.940 --> 23:36.710
on one of those kids again,
you're off the task force.

23:36.910 --> 23:38.680
<i>* *</i>

23:38.880 --> 23:40.180
Yeah.

23:40.380 --> 23:47.350
<i>* *</i>

23:55.900 --> 23:58.830
[fires crackling]

24:06.540 --> 24:07.910
[door opens]

24:08.110 --> 24:10.910
<i>[tense music]</i>

24:11.110 --> 24:12.380
[door closes]

24:12.580 --> 24:17.820
<i>* *</i>

24:18.020 --> 24:19.490
- You know,
we have questions too.

24:19.690 --> 24:22.160
I wish I had the answers.

24:22.360 --> 24:25.830
To be honest, we don't know
much more about this than you.

24:26.030 --> 24:28.500
Well, what about them?

24:28.700 --> 24:31.300
Haven't they been, like...

24:31.500 --> 24:32.630
You can say it.

24:32.830 --> 24:33.940
I'm not saying it.

24:34.130 --> 24:35.700
- You're gonna have to say it
eventually.

24:35.900 --> 24:37.410
- You're like us now.
- [scoffs]

24:37.610 --> 24:40.540
- I'm definitely not like you.
[liquid sloshes]

24:40.740 --> 24:42.640
<i>* *</i>

24:42.840 --> 24:43.750
- I need to talk
with these guys

24:43.940 --> 24:45.780
alone for a minute.

24:45.980 --> 24:47.550
Don't go anywhere. Okay?

24:47.750 --> 24:52.690
<i>* *</i>

24:52.890 --> 24:53.820
Guys.

24:54.020 --> 25:01.160
<i>* *</i>

25:01.460 --> 25:04.970
[coughing]

25:05.170 --> 25:07.840
[groaning and sniffling]

25:08.040 --> 25:10.710
- You shouldn't have checked
yourself out of the hospital.

25:10.910 --> 25:13.880
- [coughs] I'm fine.
[sniffles]

25:14.070 --> 25:16.850
Listen to me.

25:17.040 --> 25:18.880
Blake's right.
They're not like you.

25:19.080 --> 25:20.280
They were bitten.

25:20.480 --> 25:22.620
The rules could be
completely different for them.

25:22.820 --> 25:24.620
I said the same thing.

25:24.820 --> 25:26.150
We don't know
what's gonna happen to them

25:26.350 --> 25:27.690
on the night of a full moon.

25:27.890 --> 25:30.090
- But nothing's ever happened
to us on a full moon.

25:30.290 --> 25:32.790
I wouldn't say nothing.

25:32.990 --> 25:35.100
<i>* *</i>

25:35.300 --> 25:37.970
It was a full moon
the night I found you.

25:38.170 --> 25:39.770
What are you guys feeling
right now?

25:39.970 --> 25:41.840
Anything different?

25:42.040 --> 25:43.640
- When Everett
was being questioned,

25:43.840 --> 25:48.240
we were in separate rooms,
but we could hear each other.

25:48.440 --> 25:50.750
Like, we could all
hear each other.

25:50.950 --> 25:52.780
- You mean the way
Harlan can hear?

25:52.980 --> 25:54.150
It's like we were sharing it.

25:54.350 --> 25:55.750
- It's because we're a pack.
We're connected.

25:55.950 --> 25:57.490
We're not connected.

25:57.690 --> 25:59.990
- Okay? We barely even know them.
- Was it just the hearing?

26:00.190 --> 26:01.260
Did you guys see anything

26:01.460 --> 26:03.830
or sense anything else
about them?

26:04.020 --> 26:05.930
Our eyes.

26:06.130 --> 26:07.130
When we were together
for the first time

26:07.330 --> 26:09.900
in the woods,
our eyes were glowing.

26:10.100 --> 26:11.200
<i>* *</i>

26:11.400 --> 26:15.540
- Glowing?
Jesus.

26:15.740 --> 26:19.540
Okay.
Anything else?

26:19.740 --> 26:20.780
Like what?

26:20.980 --> 26:23.810
<i>* *</i>

26:24.010 --> 26:25.550
I don't know.

26:25.750 --> 26:27.050
Are you trying to ask us

26:27.250 --> 26:29.880
if we think they're gonna turn
into actual werewolves?

26:30.080 --> 26:31.790
Like, grow fangs and hair

26:31.990 --> 26:34.060
and run around in the woods
and kill some fucking deer?

26:34.250 --> 26:38.930
- If they do, let's hope
that's all they kill.

26:39.130 --> 26:42.060
- We have never killed anything
before.

26:42.260 --> 26:44.800
- You've never had
a pack before.

26:45.000 --> 26:47.670
<i>[eerie music]</i>

26:47.870 --> 26:54.710
<i>* *</i>

27:29.910 --> 27:31.850
- He's not answering.
- Hmm?

27:32.050 --> 27:33.080
He's not answering.

27:34.720 --> 27:35.820
I can't wait any longer.

27:36.020 --> 27:37.850
I gotta go see
if I can find him.

27:38.050 --> 27:39.550
Um...

27:43.930 --> 27:46.330
[sighs softly]

27:46.530 --> 27:47.590
Well...

27:49.860 --> 27:51.500
It's still the full moon.

27:54.370 --> 27:57.310
Maybe we should stay.

27:57.500 --> 27:59.870
I mean, if it's really
coming after us...

28:00.070 --> 28:02.110
<i>* *</i>

28:02.310 --> 28:03.750
I don't want to be
anywhere near Danny.

28:03.940 --> 28:08.020
- So you're starting to believe
all of this now?

28:08.220 --> 28:10.750
No.

28:10.950 --> 28:13.790
[sighs]

28:13.990 --> 28:15.490
But...

28:15.690 --> 28:17.590
<i>* *</i>

28:17.790 --> 28:19.490
What?

28:19.690 --> 28:21.460
<i>* *</i>

28:21.660 --> 28:24.600
- He called me too.
The voice on the phone.

28:24.800 --> 28:26.840
He left me a message
on the motel phone.

28:27.030 --> 28:29.900
<i>* *</i>

28:30.100 --> 28:32.840
What did he say?

28:33.040 --> 28:35.840
He said, "You're not safe."

28:36.040 --> 28:37.480
But I've been thinking,

28:37.680 --> 28:40.820
what if the message
wasn't meant for me?

28:41.020 --> 28:43.890
What if it was meant
for my dad and Danny?

28:44.080 --> 28:45.890
That they're not safe?

28:46.090 --> 28:47.690
From me.

28:47.890 --> 28:51.730
<i>* *</i>

28:51.930 --> 28:53.030
[door opens]

28:53.230 --> 28:54.300
<i>Tell that bitch</i>

28:54.490 --> 28:56.100
<i>I just drove</i>
<i>three miles on rims.</i>

28:56.300 --> 28:57.230
<i>She thinks</i>
<i>she can slash my tires</i>

28:57.430 --> 28:58.630
<i>and just walk away?</i>

28:58.830 --> 29:01.400
<i>Absolutely not.</i>
<i>I am gonna fucking ruin her.</i>

29:01.600 --> 29:03.570
- <i>[phone beeps]</i>
- [scoffs]

29:03.770 --> 29:05.040
Why is she calling me?

29:05.240 --> 29:06.570
- Because she doesn't have
a phone.

29:06.770 --> 29:08.780
- You didn't really slash
her tires, did you?

29:08.980 --> 29:11.050
- How could she?
She's been here the whole time.

29:11.250 --> 29:12.750
- Does anyone have
Phoebe's address?

29:12.950 --> 29:14.380
- I do.
- Text me.

29:14.580 --> 29:15.750
Okay.

29:18.990 --> 29:20.190
Don't ask.

29:20.390 --> 29:21.220
- You slept with her boyfriend
in her own house?

29:21.420 --> 29:23.420
He said don't ask.

29:23.620 --> 29:25.660
- Now, Everett, Blake, I want
you two to call your parents

29:25.860 --> 29:27.200
and tell them you're staying
with us tonight.

29:27.390 --> 29:28.400
- But--
- I'm grounded.

29:28.600 --> 29:29.500
- I'm supposed to watch
my brother.

29:29.700 --> 29:31.070
- Okay.
Then give me 20 minutes.

29:31.270 --> 29:34.000
Just gotta check
if this girl's okay.

29:34.200 --> 29:35.240
Lock everything behind me.

29:35.440 --> 29:36.970
- What about Connor?
- What about us?

29:37.170 --> 29:38.210
20 minutes.

29:38.410 --> 29:41.240
[engine revving]

29:41.440 --> 29:43.110
<i>* *</i>

29:43.310 --> 29:45.650
[tires squeal]

29:45.850 --> 29:52.920
<i>* *</i>

29:53.250 --> 29:55.120
- Sorry, but I have
another question.

29:55.320 --> 29:56.360
The voice on the phone said
it had to kill us

29:56.560 --> 29:57.530
before the next full moon.

29:57.720 --> 29:58.930
Does that mean we're okay now?

29:59.130 --> 30:00.660
Is it supposed to kill us
before the full moon,

30:00.860 --> 30:02.500
during the full moon,
or when the sun rises?

30:02.700 --> 30:03.900
How are we supposed to know?

30:04.100 --> 30:06.130
- Because you're--

30:06.330 --> 30:07.430
Twins?

30:09.940 --> 30:11.810
- Our senses are turned up
during the full moon.

30:12.010 --> 30:14.940
In the morning,
we're back to normal.

30:15.140 --> 30:16.010
So we're not safe yet?

30:16.210 --> 30:18.110
<i>* *</i>

30:18.310 --> 30:21.750
We've still got
the rest of the night?

30:21.950 --> 30:23.180
To die.

30:23.380 --> 30:26.050
<i>[tense music]</i>

30:26.250 --> 30:33.330
<i>* *</i>

30:39.500 --> 30:41.770
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

30:41.970 --> 30:44.810
[insects droning]

30:54.750 --> 30:56.890
- It's okay.
Nothing's out there.

30:57.080 --> 30:58.190
You sure?

30:58.390 --> 31:00.650
- Hey, how much
can you actually hear?

31:00.850 --> 31:02.360
- It depends.
It's better on a full moon.

31:02.560 --> 31:04.360
- What else can you do?
- What do you mean?

31:04.560 --> 31:06.030
Like, your hearing.

31:06.230 --> 31:07.430
Is there anything
else you can do?

31:07.630 --> 31:10.660
She can run fast.
Like, really fast.

31:10.860 --> 31:12.470
Good for her.

31:13.330 --> 31:14.470
He's strong.

31:15.500 --> 31:17.070
<i>* *</i>

31:17.270 --> 31:18.710
How strong?

31:18.910 --> 31:20.470
<i>* *</i>

31:20.670 --> 31:25.050
- I kind of put my fist
through a support beam.

31:25.250 --> 31:26.610
It was big.

31:26.810 --> 31:29.050
<i>* *</i>

31:29.250 --> 31:31.990
- Yeah.
What about you?

31:32.190 --> 31:33.790
Smell.

31:33.990 --> 31:35.060
That's kind of gross.

31:35.260 --> 31:36.720
Yeah.

31:36.920 --> 31:38.930
Can be.

31:39.130 --> 31:43.830
- Wait, so is it like
we each have one ability?

31:44.030 --> 31:45.370
I don't get it.

31:45.570 --> 31:47.500
When we were with the cops,
you could all hear like me.

31:47.700 --> 31:50.370
- Maybe it's like
when we're together we sync up.

31:50.570 --> 31:52.270
- It's because we're connected.
We're a pack.

31:52.470 --> 31:54.140
- Enough of the pack shit,
Luna.

31:54.340 --> 31:57.450
Can you two still hear like me?

31:57.640 --> 31:59.980
Wait, let me try something.

32:00.180 --> 32:02.180
<i>[phone chimes]</i>
I put on a high-frequency tone.

32:02.380 --> 32:03.650
<i>[high-pitched ringing]</i>

32:03.850 --> 32:05.190
I don't hear anything.
Do you?

32:05.390 --> 32:08.390
<i>[high-pitched ringing]</i>

32:08.590 --> 32:10.590
Turn it off, please.

32:10.790 --> 32:11.730
<i>[high-pitched ringing]</i>

32:11.930 --> 32:13.530
Oh.

32:13.730 --> 32:14.800
<i>[high-pitched ringing stops]</i>

32:15.900 --> 32:20.070
- Wait.
- You hear something?

32:20.270 --> 32:23.340
- No.
- You smell something?

32:23.540 --> 32:25.970
<i>* *</i>

32:26.170 --> 32:27.940
There's something out there.

32:28.140 --> 32:30.880
<i>[tense music]</i>

32:31.080 --> 32:37.050
<i>* *</i>

32:37.250 --> 32:38.890
I got that too.

32:39.090 --> 32:45.960
<i>* *</i>

32:47.330 --> 32:49.330
It smells like...

32:49.530 --> 32:51.300
Acid.

32:51.500 --> 32:53.670
- That's exactly
what it smells like.

32:53.870 --> 32:55.200
What?

32:55.400 --> 32:57.610
<i>* *</i>

32:57.800 --> 32:58.910
Anger.

32:59.110 --> 33:04.210
<i>* *</i>

33:04.410 --> 33:06.410
<i>[tense music fades]</i>

33:14.020 --> 33:15.360
[loud pounding at door]

33:15.560 --> 33:18.660
[all gasping and panting]

33:18.860 --> 33:20.630
- Don't open it.
- Why?

33:20.830 --> 33:22.600
- You don't know
who's out there.

33:22.800 --> 33:24.300
- I'm pretty sure the werewolf
wouldn't bother knocking

33:24.500 --> 33:26.300
before he comes
to rip us apart.

33:26.500 --> 33:27.700
You said "werewolf."

33:27.900 --> 33:29.100
- [sighs]
Go fuck yourself.

33:29.300 --> 33:30.470
[loud pounding at door]

33:30.670 --> 33:33.870
- This is Officer Trent Miller
with the LAPD.

33:34.070 --> 33:36.540
I need to ask
a few follow-up questions.

33:36.740 --> 33:38.310
- Isn't that the guy
you assaulted?

33:38.510 --> 33:40.610
- He assaulted me.
- His name's Trent?

33:40.810 --> 33:42.750
- [loud pounding at door]
- I know you're in there.

33:42.950 --> 33:45.990
I could see you
through the windows.

33:46.190 --> 33:47.320
Just here to talk.

33:47.520 --> 33:49.060
- You don't have
to talk to him.

33:49.260 --> 33:50.930
- He knows we're here.
- It doesn't matter.

33:51.120 --> 33:52.260
If you tell the cops
they can't come in,

33:52.460 --> 33:53.830
they legally can't.

33:54.030 --> 33:57.230
<i>* *</i>

33:57.430 --> 33:58.370
You can't come in.

33:58.570 --> 33:59.630
That's fine by me.

33:59.830 --> 34:01.600
Let's talk out here.

34:01.800 --> 34:03.540
Five minutes, guys.
That's all I need.

34:03.740 --> 34:05.840
Come on.
Open the door.

34:06.040 --> 34:07.580
<i>* *</i>

34:07.770 --> 34:09.640
- Go into the office
down the hall.

34:09.840 --> 34:11.010
I don't want this guy
to know you're here.

34:11.210 --> 34:12.680
- What are you gonna do?
- I'm thinking.

34:12.880 --> 34:13.850
Go!

34:14.050 --> 34:15.980
- We're all
on the same side here.

34:16.180 --> 34:18.250
We're all just trying
to figure out...

34:18.450 --> 34:21.160
- Go.
- Who started the fire.

34:21.360 --> 34:23.960
We'll never bother you again.

34:24.160 --> 34:26.060
Promise.

34:26.260 --> 34:28.400
<i>* *</i>

34:28.600 --> 34:30.430
[latch clicks]

34:30.630 --> 34:33.400
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

34:33.600 --> 34:35.140
<i>* *</i>

34:35.340 --> 34:37.200
[insects droning]

34:41.880 --> 34:43.540
[sighs]

34:43.740 --> 34:50.820
<i>* *</i>

35:26.820 --> 35:29.090
Are you still feeling it?

35:29.290 --> 35:31.460
<i>[soft ominous music]</i>

35:31.660 --> 35:32.830
<i>* *</i>

35:33.030 --> 35:35.200
- The full moon?
- Uh, yeah.

35:35.400 --> 35:38.070
[chuckles nervously]
Definitely still feeling it.

35:38.270 --> 35:39.700
<i>* *</i>

35:46.110 --> 35:48.140
[panting]

35:48.340 --> 35:49.610
Did you set the fire?

35:49.810 --> 35:51.280
- I told you.
I don't know anything.

35:51.480 --> 35:53.250
Let's try that again.

35:53.450 --> 35:55.120
Did you set the fire?

35:55.320 --> 35:57.720
- Dude. Get your hands--
- Mother--

35:57.920 --> 36:00.150
No, Dad, he's outside.

36:00.350 --> 36:02.260
He's talking to him right now.

36:02.460 --> 36:03.590
Yeah, it's the same cop.

36:03.790 --> 36:05.590
[tires squealing]

36:05.790 --> 36:07.400
<i>* *</i>

36:07.590 --> 36:08.800
- Okay.
I'm on my way back.

36:09.000 --> 36:10.360
Did the cop say anything?

36:10.560 --> 36:12.630
- He said he just wanted
to ask some questions.

36:12.830 --> 36:16.340
Did you set the fire?

36:16.540 --> 36:18.540
- [groans]
- Tell me...

36:18.740 --> 36:20.840
the fucking truth!

36:21.040 --> 36:22.810
<i>[high-pitched ringing]</i>

36:23.010 --> 36:25.980
<i>[tense music]</i>

36:26.180 --> 36:29.050
[approaching
galloping footsteps]

36:29.250 --> 36:30.880
[werewolf roars]

36:31.080 --> 36:32.820
- [grunts]
[bodies thud]

36:33.020 --> 36:35.960
[rustling]

36:36.160 --> 36:37.460
<i>* *</i>

36:37.660 --> 36:42.260
[panting]

36:42.460 --> 36:44.200
The cop.
It took the fucking cop.

36:44.400 --> 36:45.370
- What?
- It's outside.

36:45.570 --> 36:46.870
It's right outside the house.

36:47.070 --> 36:48.440
- Dad.
Dad, did you hear that?

36:48.640 --> 36:50.740
<i>- Harlan!</i>
- What do we do?

36:50.940 --> 36:52.070
<i>- Can you get to the stable</i>
<i>outside?</i>

36:52.270 --> 36:53.270
What's in the stable?

36:53.470 --> 36:55.040
<i>Harlan, listen to me,</i>

36:55.240 --> 36:57.450
it's ten steps
from the kitchen door.

36:57.640 --> 36:58.450
You can make it.

36:58.650 --> 37:00.010
<i>I need you to get the rifle.</i>

37:00.210 --> 37:01.420
The rifle in your office?

37:01.620 --> 37:03.780
- Not that one.
It's in the stable.

37:03.980 --> 37:06.120
- But the rifle's
in the gun case in the office.

37:06.320 --> 37:07.620
<i>This one is different.</i>

37:07.820 --> 37:09.020
I'll explain later.

37:09.220 --> 37:11.960
It's in the supply cabinet
in the stable, all right?

37:12.160 --> 37:15.530
<i>[</i>

37:15.730 --> 37:22.600
<i>* *</i>

37:33.180 --> 37:34.880
[sighs]

37:35.080 --> 37:36.520
<i>* *</i>

37:36.720 --> 37:37.950
Go.

37:38.150 --> 37:43.020
<i>* *</i>

37:43.220 --> 37:46.260
<i>[tense music fading]</i>

37:49.430 --> 37:52.870
I don't hear them.

37:53.070 --> 37:55.540
Luna?

37:55.740 --> 38:00.140
- We gotta get out of here.
- Okay. What about the cop?

38:00.340 --> 38:01.780
We'll go out the back door.

38:09.550 --> 38:11.650
- What about Harlan and Luna?
- [scoffs softly]

38:11.850 --> 38:13.620
They don't seem to be too
concerned about us right now.

38:13.820 --> 38:15.220
- Okay, but what
if it's still out there?

38:15.420 --> 38:17.290
- There's nothing out there,
Everett.

38:17.490 --> 38:19.590
If you want to stay, fine.
But I'm going.

38:19.790 --> 38:22.630
[phone buzzing]

38:25.470 --> 38:26.830
<i>- [distorted voice]</i>
<i>Don't leave the house.</i>

38:27.030 --> 38:29.340
- Who are you?
<i>- You're almost safe.</i>

38:29.540 --> 38:31.170
<i>The moon is past its peak.</i>

38:31.370 --> 38:32.970
Are you watching us?

38:33.170 --> 38:34.170
Is it still trying to kill us?

38:34.370 --> 38:36.680
<i>Don't leave the house.</i>

38:36.880 --> 38:40.750
<i>* *</i>

38:40.950 --> 38:43.680
[insects droning]

38:43.880 --> 38:47.190
<i>* *</i>

38:47.390 --> 38:50.120
[coughing]

38:50.320 --> 38:53.090
<i>[dissonant tense music]</i>

38:53.290 --> 39:00.370
<i>* *</i>

39:07.140 --> 39:08.580
[grunts]

39:08.780 --> 39:12.610
<i>* *</i>

39:12.810 --> 39:13.710
[groans]

39:13.910 --> 39:17.720
<i>* *</i>

39:17.920 --> 39:20.690
[groans and coughs]

39:20.890 --> 39:27.760
<i>* *</i>

39:41.780 --> 39:43.910
<i>- All right, tactical case.</i>
<i>Supply cabinet.</i>

39:44.110 --> 39:45.380
- <i>You see it?</i>
- Harlan.

39:45.580 --> 39:48.750
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

39:48.950 --> 39:51.080
- [combination lock clicks]
- What's the combination?

39:51.280 --> 39:52.690
- Dad, how do you open
the case?

39:52.890 --> 39:54.150
- [whispering]
The combination!

39:54.350 --> 39:55.590
<i>All right, it's six numbers.</i>

39:55.790 --> 39:57.690
- <i>Luna, are you listening?</i>
- Yeah.

39:57.890 --> 40:00.990
<i>- 34, 21...</i>
[combination lock clicking]

40:01.190 --> 40:07.270
<i>16, 42, 26, 32.</i>

40:07.470 --> 40:10.600
[horse snorting softly]

40:10.800 --> 40:12.370
<i>[high-pitched ringing]</i>

40:12.570 --> 40:14.010
[horse snorts]

40:14.210 --> 40:16.240
<i>* *</i>

40:16.440 --> 40:19.210
[horse snorting in agitation]

40:19.410 --> 40:22.420
<i>[dissonant tense music]</i>

40:22.620 --> 40:23.480
[horse neighs loudly]

40:23.680 --> 40:25.250
- Luna.
- Huh?

40:25.450 --> 40:26.850
What's the combination?

40:27.050 --> 40:29.360
<i>* *</i>

40:29.560 --> 40:32.730
- Luna.
<i>- Harlan, can you hear me?</i>

40:32.930 --> 40:36.030
<i>* *</i>

40:36.230 --> 40:39.130
- [screaming, grunting]
[werewolf snarling]

40:39.330 --> 40:42.140
<i>[tense music]</i>

40:42.340 --> 40:43.400
<i>* *</i>

40:43.600 --> 40:45.270
[werewolf snarls]

40:45.470 --> 40:49.010
<i>* *</i>

40:49.210 --> 40:51.410
[bones crack]
[screaming]

40:51.610 --> 40:55.280
<i>* *</i>

40:55.480 --> 40:56.720
[screams]

40:56.920 --> 40:58.520
[wet crunch]

41:02.920 --> 41:05.560
[bolt clicking]

41:11.330 --> 41:14.170
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

41:14.370 --> 41:21.440
<i>* *</i>

41:38.120 --> 41:42.200
- I think he said
not to leave the house.

41:42.400 --> 41:44.100
- You think we're safe
in there?

41:44.300 --> 41:46.130
<i>* *</i>

41:46.330 --> 41:49.200
We're not safe anywhere.

41:49.400 --> 41:56.480
<i>* *</i>

42:04.850 --> 42:05.890
Blake.

42:09.290 --> 42:11.020
[werewolf growls]

42:11.220 --> 42:13.360
[slow footsteps]

42:13.560 --> 42:16.030
[werewolf snarling]

42:16.230 --> 42:18.970
[approaching steady footsteps]

42:19.170 --> 42:21.230
[low growling]

42:21.430 --> 42:24.170
[approaching steady footsteps]

42:24.370 --> 42:25.870
<i>* *</i>

42:26.070 --> 42:28.380
[werewolf snarls]

42:28.570 --> 42:35.650
<i>* *</i>

42:39.350 --> 42:42.190
[werewolf snarling]

42:42.390 --> 42:49.000
<i>* *</i>

42:49.200 --> 42:52.170
[low growl]

42:53.130 --> 42:57.170
[slow footsteps]

42:57.370 --> 42:58.940
[gunshot]

42:59.140 --> 43:06.010
<i>* *</i>

43:10.020 --> 43:12.050
[gasping]

43:15.960 --> 43:18.230
- Wh-why...

43:18.420 --> 43:20.330
why didn't it kill me?

43:20.530 --> 43:22.830
- Maybe that's not
what it wants.

43:23.030 --> 43:25.930
Not anymore.

43:26.130 --> 43:29.300
- Then what the fuck
does it want?

43:29.500 --> 43:31.670
- Well, why would it try
and kill us at Blake's house?

43:31.870 --> 43:34.470
And now it just takes off?

43:34.670 --> 43:36.380
[panting]

43:36.580 --> 43:39.110
Because we're connected.

43:39.310 --> 43:41.210
We're part of its pack.

43:41.410 --> 43:43.680
[tense musical crescendo]

43:55.230 --> 43:58.070
Are you okay?

43:58.260 --> 43:59.330
What happened?

43:59.530 --> 44:02.340
<i>[soft tense music]</i>

44:02.540 --> 44:08.740
<i>* *</i>

44:08.940 --> 44:10.010
These are silver.

44:10.210 --> 44:13.310
<i>* *</i>

44:13.510 --> 44:15.020
Real silver.

44:15.210 --> 44:19.090
<i>* *</i>

44:19.290 --> 44:22.090
Yes.

44:22.290 --> 44:24.120
You made these?

44:24.320 --> 44:25.490
Yes.

44:25.690 --> 44:28.960
To kill werewolves?

44:29.160 --> 44:30.960
Yes.

44:31.160 --> 44:34.000
<i>* *</i>

44:34.200 --> 44:36.170
To kill us?

44:36.370 --> 44:43.140
<i>* *</i>

44:43.710 --> 44:45.650
Yes.

44:45.850 --> 44:49.080
<i>* *</i>

45:07.700 --> 45:08.640
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

45:08.840 --> 45:10.370
- When I found
the two of you...

45:10.570 --> 45:12.570
[horse snorts and neighs]
You were both cubs.

45:13.040 --> 45:14.710
I saw that thing up close.

45:14.910 --> 45:16.080
<i>[high-pitched ringing]</i>

45:16.280 --> 45:17.640
<i>* *</i>

45:17.840 --> 45:19.610
- It's not gonna kill us?
- It's protecting us.

45:19.810 --> 45:20.680
Werewolf!

45:20.880 --> 45:22.280
<i>* *</i>

45:25.290 --> 45:28.120
<i>[tense music]</i>

45:28.320 --> 45:35.200
<i>* *</i>
